<title>UPDATE-PARAMETER-REPEATEDLY</title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Language" content="en-gb">
</head>

<body>

<h3><i>I update a parameter repeatedly.</i> </h3>
<font size="2" color="gray">Begin micro-behaviour</font>
<p><b>UPDATE-PARAMETER-REPEATEDLY</b></p>
<font size="2" color="gray">Begin NetLogo code:</font>
<pre>substitute-text-area-for parameter-name the-parameter                   
substitute-text-area-for parameter-expression the-parameter + 1                                         
substitute-text-area-for time-period 1                                                 
substitute-text-area-for comment Notes                                                                      
do-every time-period
   [set parameter-name 
        parameter-expression]
;comment</pre>
<font size="2" color="gray">End NetLogo code</font>
<h2>Variants</h2>
<p>You can change the name and the expression for updating the parameter.</p>
<h2>Related Micro-behaviours</h2>
<p><a href="DEFINE-PARAMETER.html">DEFINE-PARAMETER</a> defines parameters that 
this behaviour updates. <a href="UPDATE-PARAMETER.html">UPDATE-PARAMETER</a> 
updates parameters once. <a href="UPDATE-ATTRIBUTE-REPEATEDLY.html">UPDATE-ATTRIBUTE-REPEATEDLY</a> 
updates an attribute of an agent repeatedly.</p>
<h2>How this works</h2>
<p>This uses the NetLogo <b>SET</b> primitive command to update the value of the 
parameter. It uses the BehaviourComposer <b>
	<a target="_blank" href="http://resources.modelling4all.org/documents/programming-guide#toc0">
	do-every</a></b> command to schedule the 
updates repeatedly.</p>
<h2>History</h2>
<p>This was implemented by Ken Kahn on 27 October 2009.</p>

